Getting started

GitHub Pages can automatically generate and serve the website for you. Letâ€™s say you have a username/organisation my-org and project my-proj; if you locate Jekyll source under docs folder of master branch in your repo github.com/my-org/my-proj, the website will be served on my-org.github.io/my-proj. The good thing about coupling your documentation with the source repo is, whenever you merge features with regarding content to master branch, it will also be published on the webpage instantly.
